<br>
Rapid Feign, ok if you have to split out 15 casters this could be useful, but 99% of the pulls I've done I havent needed RF.<br>
<br>
Dragon Punch, theyre rooting everything now, so whats the point of trying to push it.<br>
<br>
Critical Mend, this could be nice, but 50% heal is still only once every mend refresh, maybe.<br>
<br>
Ambidexterous, we think its like what 6-8% damage increase, wont help much if your dead.<br>
<br>
Just seems to me the Arch skills like Natural Durability, avoidance and mitigation and regens are much better. The class skills seem to be there for particular encounters or something cause they just arent practical in standard use.  <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8148">Sikanak Shadowscale</a><br>
